HOUSE RESOLUTION 65
By Parkinson
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Richard Ransom of
Memphis.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should salute those citizens who, through their
extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as community leaders of whom we can all
be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy person is Richard Ransom, a highly respected
journalist, television news anchor, and community advocate who has enriched the lives of the
citizens in the Memphis area for many years; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Ransom's journey began in Peoria, Illinois, moving on to Jacksonville,
Florida, before ultimately landing in Memphis; apart from a three-year stint in Milwaukee,
Wisconsin, he has dedicated nearly his entire professional life to being a trusted information
source for the citizens of Bluff City, earning numerous Emmy awards for his outstanding
contributions to journalism along the way; and
WHEREAS, his career started as a researcher for the ABC News London bureau, a role
that laid the foundation for his passion for storytelling and investigative reporting; and
WHEREAS, during his time at WATN-TV in Memphis, Richard Ransom has been a
cornerstone of the newsroom, breaking major stories, conducting exclusive interviews, and
sharing his wealth of institutional knowledge; his leadership and unwavering commitment have
made him a trusted voice for both routine and breaking news coverage; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Ransom's enthusiasm for politics has shone through his role as a host
for statewide televised debates, including those for U.S. Senate and Tennessee gubernatorial
races; most recently, he earned widespread acclaim for moderating what many considered the
standout debate of the Memphis mayoral race; and
